---
import SectionHeading from "./SectionHeading.astro";

const points = [
  {
    title: "Open source",
    body: "AGPL-3.0. Every reviewer, every verdict, the whole gate. Nothing about how your code is judged is hidden behind a service.",
  },
  {
    title: "Self-hostable",
    body: "Runs anywhere code can run, local or any CI. It drives the agent backends you already use (Claude Code, Codex) and reuses your own auth and billing.",
  },
  {
    title: "No lock-in",
    body: "Your policy is one declarative file in your repo. Take it with you. There's no proprietary format and no black box to migrate off of.",
  },
];
---

<section class="section trust" id="open">
  <div class="container">
    <SectionHeading title="Inspectable, not just trusted.">
      The closed reviewers sell you a SOC 2 badge and a vanity counter, and bill
      you for the privilege. Bastion offers something you can verify yourself:
      read every reviewer, run it on your own infrastructure through the model
      provider and billing you already use, and own the gate outright.
    </SectionHeading>

    <div class="trust-grid">
      {
        points.map((p, i) => (
          <article class="trust-card" data-reveal style={`--reveal-delay:${i * 70}ms`}>
            <h3>{p.title}</h3>
            <p>{p.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))
      }
    </div>

    <div class="honest" data-reveal>
      <div class="honest-mark" aria-hidden="true">
        <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
          <path d="M12 3 4 6v6c0 4.5 3.2 7.3 8 9 4.8-1.7 8-4.5 8-9V6l-8-3Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
          <path d="M9.2 12.2l1.9 1.9 3.9-4.2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div class="honest-body">
        <h3>We'd rather block than pretend.</h3>
        <p>
          Bastion is early software and evolving fast. The runner, the gate, and
          the Claude Code and Codex backends execute reviewers for real, and
          anything not yet wired <strong>fails closed</strong> rather than
          pretending. An unimplemented reviewer never claims to have reviewed
          anything. That honesty is the whole point of a gate.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .trust-grid {
    margin-top: clamp(2rem, 1rem + 3vw, 3rem);
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 760px) {
    .trust-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }
  .trust-card {
    padding: clamp(1.1rem, 0.8rem + 1vw, 1.5rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
    border-radius: var(--radius-3);
    background: var(--paper-raised);
  }
  .trust-card h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .trust-card p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }

  .honest {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 0.9rem + 1.4vw, 1.8rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--pass-line);
    border-radius: var(--radius-3);
    background: linear-gradient(
      to bottom right,
      var(--pass-bg),
      var(--paper-raised) 55%
    );
  }
  .honest-mark {
    flex: none;
    color: var(--pass-ink);
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
  }
  .honest-body h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .honest-body p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--ink-2);
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
</style>
